OL,3,CHalifax worker sentenced for stealing
OL,4,Cthousands to fund gambling addiction
OL,6,FIn a statement, Halifax said: "We take
OL,7,Fprotecting our customers' money
OL,8,Fextremely seriously and co-operated
OL,9,Ffully with the authorities, while
OL,10,Fensuring there was no financial loss
OL,11,Fto customers."
OL,13,FRecorder Eleanor Hourigan ordered
OL,14,FOlivier to complete a community order
OL,15,Fof 180 hours of unpaid work.
OL,17,FShe said that because he had paid the
OL,18,Fmoney back and shown genuine remorse
OL,19,Fhe had avoided a suspended prison
OL,20,Fsentence.
